Adding visual KPI's on the dashboard

Adding some Key Performance indicators on the dashboard:

We want to show the total  Sessions on our site. How many hits do we get per preuser per day. Using the different slicers we will see which pages were mostly clicked on, Users with most sessions etc.

Steps:

1.  Click on the card visual to select it

2 Click to add the Total Session Count column in the Field tab, using the downward pointer, select the 'Count' function



We want to show how many pages on Average our PreUsers click on when they land on our site

Steps:

1.  Click on the card visual to select it

2 Click to  add the PageCnt column to in the field tab

3. Click on the Pointer and select 'Average' as an aggregate


We want to show the Average number of minutes spent on website.

Steps:

1.  Click on the Gauge visual to select it

2 Click to  add the TotalSessionMin column to in the field tab

3. Click on the Pointer and select 'Average' as an aggregate



The dash board is now complete. Use the Filters to interact with the data to get more insights. Good job!!
